{
  "stem": "10829.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And [NON-ENGLISH] was a little bit closer, but [NON-ENGLISH] was where we used to go to the next big town to catch trains or to deal the market.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "That was already the big city to us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And it lays near Katowice, which is a big city, and that's [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And it was basically an all-Jewish town, a shtetl.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My family life in-- in Polish, in Poland, where I come from, the shtetl was real simple.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had-- I'll give you more or less a description of it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was-- it's a one-street town.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You go, and it was a thoroughfare.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that was like-- Columbus, Ohio, I would compare it to Route 40, which it would start at one end of the United States and go to the other one.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Trochenbrod was a-- was set around that street.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So what we had is houses on one side, and houses on the other side, and your land, or the fields, used to be in the back of the house, as far as your eyes could see.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was your land, and your house was in the front.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then the richer people or whatever would have some fields on the outskirts.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now, we were surrounded with [NON-ENGLISH], villages, Polish and Ukraines, which were-- used to be surrounded around us, and we were right sort of in the middle.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we had three, about five schuls in our town.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The houses were pretty far away.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And our house was just about in the middle of the town.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Like the post office was almost right across the street from us, And the city well, which most of our people from there used to go, and you'd have to go-- take the [YIDDISH], they'd call it in Yiddish, which is a well.",
      "word_count": 43
    }
  ],
